    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen calling `vim.lsp.document_color.enable()` with any text, besides `background`, `foreground`, etc., in the style option the text appears before the hex color code.\n\n<img width=\"1040\" height=\"608\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7773c1bb-20d9-4c86-995c-e6da34a46987\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim --clean -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n```\nlocal pattern = \"lua\"\nlocal cmd = { \"lua-language-server\" }\nlocal root_markers = { \".git\", \".editorconfig\" }\nlocal settings = vim.empty_dict()\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"FileType\", {\n\tpattern = pattern,\n\tcallback = function(args)\n\t\tlocal match = vim.fs.find(root_markers, { path = args.file, upward = true })[1]\n\t\tlocal root_dir = match and vim.fn.fnamemodify(match, \":p:h\") or nil\n\t\tvim.lsp.start({\n\t\t\tname = \"bugged-ls\",\n\t\t\tcmd = cmd,\n\t\t\troot_dir = root_dir,\n\t\t\tsettings = settings,\n\t\t})\n\tend,\n})\n```\nCmdline:\n`:lua vim.lsp.document_color.enable(true, {}, { style = 'any_text' })`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI think it should send and error message stating the wrong option value.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.2\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nlua-language-server 3.18.2-dev\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWSL: 2.7.3.0 VoidLinux rolling\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
