            "body": "This is by design. [As the docs say](https://neovim.io/doc/user/lsp/#vim.lsp.document_color.enable()):\n\n> (`style`) It can be one of the pre-defined styles, a string to be used as virtual text, or a function that receives the buffer handle, the range (start line, start col, end line, end col) and the resolved hex color.",
